The course provides an overview of the methodology of teaching English. Topics covered include learning and teaching styles and methods, lesson and syllabus development, language grammar, vocabulary and English skills development, assessment and feedback, etc.Objectives/eesmärkid:  1) Introduce basic knowledge of English teaching methodology 2) to provide students with an overview of the curriculum, the syllabus and the preparation of the teacher's work plan, the planning and targeting of lessons, and the testing, assessment and feedback of teaching English.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student:
1) is aware of the national curriculum and the syllabus of English as a Foreign Language;
2) knows and can use different methods of teaching English;
3) is able to draw up an English lesson plan taking into account the development of all basic language skills;
4) knows different teaching aids and is able to use them;
5) is familiar with different forms of evaluation and feedback.
